name: Bourbon Mustard Chicken
description: ENCORE ENTREE!!! You'll see this favorite on our menu every other month. Our chicken breasts soak in a bourbon and mustard sauce that is slightly sweet and totally delicious.

name: Cilantro-Lime Chicken Fajita
description: Strips of chicken that you season to your liking with cilantro, lime juice, and spices are great for a quick meal any day of the week. Serve with your own toppings (sour cream, salsa, etc.)

name: Crock-pot Pork Pull
description: ENCORE ENTREE!!! This meal will be on our menu every other month. It is a customer favorite! Put this easy meal in the crock-pot before you leave for the day and by the time you get home, dinner is ready. Seasoned pork shoulder that dissolves into a beautiful, shreddable (is that a word?) yummy entr√©e that is great by itself or as a sandwich.

name: Steak Fajita with Lime Pepper
description: Seasoned steak strips come with peppers, onions, and flour tortillas. They heat up quickly on your stove top or on the grill. Perfect for those nights when you need something in a flash! (Grill or stove top).

name: Green Egg Quiche
description: A delicious quiche made with broccoli, ham, and your choice of cheese is perfect for any day you want to serve a special breakfast (or lunch or dinner)for your family.

name: Sober Irish Stew
description: Chunks of lean beef, carrots, potatoes, onions, celery and our special seasonings make up this stick-to-your-ribs meal.  Add water or your favorite brew to make it special.

name: Spanish Spiced Steak
description: Coated with an intriguing rub of fresh-ground spices, broiled to perfection on a sunny day, and drizzled with a light Dijon-herb vinaigrette.

name: Herb and Veggie Turkey Meatloaf
description: A lighter version of meatloaf...this time made with ground turkey and ground pork. We add in spinach, carrots, and our seasoned tomato sauce to make a meatloaf that won't make you feel stuffed!

name: Southwest Steak and Beans
description: A spicy rub coats this ready-to-grill steak that you top with a quick-cook salsa and bean mixture.

name: Lemon-Oregano Chicken
description: These chicken breasts are rubbed with a flavorful oregano rub and are sliced thinly to cook up quickly on your stove top. You will love the lemon zest!

name: Veggie Enchilada
description: A delightful blend of diced tomatoes, green chilies, corn, black beans, onions and spices cooks in your slow cooker until you are ready to eat. Fill the corn tortillas.

name: Dilly Tilapia
description: Pan seared tilapia fillets are topped with a creamy dill sauce that is sweetened with a hint of honey.

name: Hoisin Lime Grilled Chicken
description: These zesty chicken breast cook up quickly on the grill. Hoisin sauce, soy sauce, lime juice, ginger, garlic, and dash of crushed pepper combine to form an absolutely delicious marinade.

name: Peanut Butter Shrimp with Pasta
description: Shrimp, onion, sweet red pepper and a little spinach are combined with a peanut ginger sauce and tossed with penne.

name: Popeye Pasta Ground Turkey
description: Creamy spinach and noodles topped with a rich tomato-meat sauce.

name: Popeye Pasta Ground Beef
description: Creamy spinach and noodles topped with a rich tomato-meat sauce.
